<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rascal2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rascal,</orth> adj. mean, base; good for nothing; always before a subst.: <cit><quote>some r. groom,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 671" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 671</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these r. knaves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 134</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 134</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.247" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 247</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.4.51" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.431" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 431</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.6.164" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 6, 164</bibl>. Superl. <emph>--est</emph>: <cit><quote>the most comparative, --est sweet young prince,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.90" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 90</bibl></cit> (Q<hi rend="sub">1. 2</hi> <emph>rascalliest</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>